com.vmware.esx.settings.clusters.software.reports

Interface ApplyImpact

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ApplyImpactTypes, Service
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    ApplyImpactStub

    public interface ApplyImpact
extends Service, ApplyImpactTypes
    The ApplyImpact interface provides methods to get the impact of an apply method on a cluster.

      • get

        ApplyImpactTypes.ClusterImpact get(java.lang.String cluster,
                                   ApplyImpactTypes.ApplyImpactSpec spec)
        Returns a summary of how hosts within the cluster will be impacted during an apply method. The impact is generated from the compliance information obtained from Compliance.get(java.lang.String)

        Synchronous method overload. Result of the invocation will be reported as a method return value.

        Parameters:
        cluster - The cluster identifier. The parameter must be an identifier for the resource type: ClusterComputeResource.
        spec - Specification for how much information should be returned.
        Returns:
        Summary of how hosts will be impacted during an apply method
        Throws:
        Error - If there is an unknown internal error. The accompanying error message will give more details about the failure.
        NotFound - If there is no cluster associated with cluster in the system.
        ServiceUnavailable - If the service is not available.
        Unauthenticated - if the caller is not authenticated.
        Unauthorized - if you do not have all of the privileges described as follows:
        • Method execution requires VcIntegrity.lifecycleSoftwareRemediation.Read.
        • The resource ClusterComputeResource referenced by the parameter cluster requires VcIntegrity.lifecycleSoftwareRemediation.Read.
